# gen162+gen163 (E1): the social composition that closed the last benchmark gap,
# ratcheted. Bare self-introduction "i'm vera" (gen162) fills name memory; the
# named pet "smoke" becomes the salient entity so an unbound "she/her" (gen163)
# binds to it — possession memory composing with discourse reference — and the
# query/summary read it back. Fresh vocab (vera/cat/smoke).
> hi, i'm vera
< Nice to meet you, vera!
> i have a cat named smoke
< Got it: your cat is called smoke.
> smoke is a pet
< Learned: pet(smoke).
> is she a pet?
< Yes.
> what do you know about her?
< called(cat, smoke); smoke is a pet.
> what is my name?
< Your name is vera.